reviews.review_text: Glassberg Uber Alles This may be a top 3 recording for Maistro Glassberg. If there is an award for tapers, he`s got my vote for lifetime achievement. I can`t thank him enough for recreating a period that is infamous for flat SBDs. The MOTB clean up further improves this great recording. As to the show, Garcia attacks his solos and the band cooks behind him. Early Garcia vocal flubs notwithstanding, if you like this early Brent to Phil's 6 string Modulus period (Dec'82), this is regular rotation kind of stuff.

Correction on Phil bass In 1980 Phil played his 4 string Alembic bass or another 4 string bass that was shaped like Garcia's Tiger.  

He never played 6 string electric bass until the mid 80's

A keeper Just an all-round good show -- really tight with great set lists. Great Drums>Space as well, and the show ends on a high note with an energetic, though somewhat shortened, GDTRFB.

If you didn't check, you'd think this was a SBD. Thank you Barry and Robert!
April 29, 2019 Almost fell out of my chair during Althea as the drums just bellowed across the universe

howling monkey there's that female audience member making a weird howling / screaming sound throughout, esp. in Alabama > Promised.

She was at a ton of Bay area GD and JGB shows in 79-80, she adds her own stamp to the music!

Agree, Uber Recording...But... ...Jerry is singing below par and the show just didn't grab me.  I'm panning the first set and am only keeping He's Gone through the oncore which is the only stretch I can recommend.  If it wasn't for a great capture by Barry and a modicum of reverb addition on my part to soften Jerry's vocals, I'd be passing up this show entirely.
